Interface Disposable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    HashSlotArray, HashSlotArray12byteKey, HashSlotArray16byteKey, HashSlotArray8byteKey, InternalSerializationService, LongSet, MemoryAllocator, MemoryManager
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSerializationService, HashSlotArray12byteKeyImpl, HashSlotArray16byteKeyImpl, HashSlotArray16byteKeyNoValue, HashSlotArray8byteKeyImpl, HashSlotArray8byteKeyNoValue, HashSlotArrayBase, HsaHeapMemoryManager, LongSetHsa, MemoryManagerBean, SerializationServiceV1

    @PrivateApi
public interface Disposable
    A Disposable is a container of data and/or resources that can be disposed. dispose() method is called to dispose contained data and/or resources.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void dispose()
      Disposes this object and releases any data and/or resources associated with it.

    • Method Detail

      • dispose

        void dispose()
        Disposes this object and releases any data and/or resources associated with it. If this object is already disposed then invoking this method has no effect.
